(5748,	606,	'description_overview',	'Folic Acid Helps Produce And Support New Cells Within The Body. Healthy Levels Of Folic Acid Assist With New Red Blood Cell Formation, Brain Function And Overall Health And Wellbeing. Folic Acid Isn’t Found Naturally In Food, In Australia Mandatory Fortification Of Bread Started In 2009. Folic Acid Is Different From Natural Folate, It Must Be Converted Into An Active Form Before Your Body Can Use It And Your Genetic Profile Affects How Quickly This Conversion Takes Place. For Your Body To Utilise Folic Acid It Must Be First Converted Into Active Vitamin B9, Known A 5-MTHF (5-Methyltetrahydrofolate). Lorem Ipsum Dolor Sit Amet, Consectetur Adipisicing Elit, Sed Do Eiusmod Tempor Incididunt Ut Labore Et Dolore Magna Aliqua.'),
