(638,	4,	'2020-01-19 22:16:37',	'2020-01-19 22:16:37',	'Traditional calming foods such as peppermint and ginger can be a real saviour when you’re struggling with nausea associated with morning sickness. Nibbling on homemade ginger biscuits can help to calm your stomach before, or between, meals.<br>    \r\nRead more here about eating to combat morning sickness. \r\n\r\n<strong>Ingredients:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>¾ cup oats</li>\r\n<li>¾ plain flour</li>\r\n<li>½ cup shredded coconut</li>\r\n<li>2 teaspooons ground ginger</li>\r\n<li>1 teaspoon cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>½ teaspoon nutmeg</li>\r\n<li>¼ teaspoon bicarb soda</li>\r\n<li>3 tablespoons golden syrup, melted</li>\r\n<li>2 tablespoons olive oil</li>\r\n<li>1 tablespoon milk</li>\r\n</ul> \r\n\r\n<p><strong>Method:</strong><br>\r\n1. Pre-heat oven to 160OC<br>\r\n2. Mix together all dry ingredients in a large bowl<br>\r\n3. Make a well in the centre of dry ingredients and add golden syrup, olive oil and milk<br>\r\n4. Mix together until a dough forms – if too dry add a dash more milk, if too sticky add a little extra plain four<br>\r\n5. Roll mixture into small balls and then flatten on baking tray<br>\r\n6. Bake for ~12-15 minutes, until golden<br></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Nutritional Statement:</strong><br>\r\nTraditional calming foods such as peppermint and ginger can be a real saviour when you’re struggling with nausea associated with morning sickness. Nibbling on homemade ginger biscuits can help to calm your stomach before, or between, meals.<br>    \r\nRead more here about eating to combat morning sickness. \r\n',	'Oaty Ginger Cookies',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'oaty-ginger-cookies',	'',	'',	'2020-01-20 00:57:22',	'2020-01-20 00:57:22',	'',	0,	'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=638',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
